About

Transformation is not an intervention.
It is structural design.

With over two decades of executive and advisory experience, Maya Hotait works at the intersection of governance, risk architecture, and financial sustainability — advising boards and executive leadership navigating growth, complexity, and institutional evolution across MENA, Africa, and Eurasia.

She works directly with Chairmen, CEOs, and Boards — not as an implementer, but as a strategic architect who designs the frameworks, structures, and governance systems that executive teams then own and operate.

She does not implement systems. She designs institutional architecture.

Because credibility is not claimed.
It is built.

And institutions that endure are not managed.
They are architected.
